<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4607875>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — Silicified plants from the Permian of Sardinia: A, E, Arthropitys cf. renaultii Boureau; A, transverse section of a young twig (SAR01B1B01); E, detail of the same showing the pith, primary xylem strands with carinal canals and well preserved cortex with large cells (C) in inner cortex and alternating bands of sclerenchyma and parenchyma in outer cortex (arrow); B-D, F, G, Arthropitys bistriata" ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4607875/files/figure.png" .

